4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT GENERALLY REVISING LAWS RELATED TO THE SUPERVISED
5 PRACTICE OF DENTAL HYGIENISTS; PROVIDING RULEMAKING AUTHORITY; PROVIDING A
6 DEFINITION; AND AMENDING SECTION 37-4-405, MCA.”
7
8 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
9
10 Section 1. Section 37-4-405, MCA, is amended to read:
11 "37-4-405. Dental hygienist to practice under supervision of licensed dentist -- exceptions --
12 definitions. (1) A licensed dental hygienist may:
13 (a) with the permission of the supervising dentist, practice in the office of a licensed and actively
14 practicing dentist under the general supervision of a licensed dentist; or
15 (b) provide dental hygiene preventative services in a public health facility under the general
16 supervision of a licensed dentist or, subject to the provisions of subsection (4) (3), under public health
17 supervision. ; or
18 (c) provide dental hygiene preventative services in a school-based oral health program under
19 public health supervision subject to the provisions of subsection (3).
20 (2) A dental hygienist may give instruction in oral hygiene without the direct supervision or general
21 supervision of a licensed dentist in a public or private institution or hospital or extended care facility or under a
22 board of health or in a public clinic.
23 (3) For the purposes of this section, the following definitions apply:
24 "direct supervision" means treatment by a dental auxiliary or licensed dental hygienist provided with the
25 intent and knowledge of the dentist. The treatment must be performed while the dentist is on the premises.
26 "general supervision" means treatment by a licensed dental hygienist provided with the intent and
27 knowledge of the dentist licensed and residing in the state of Montana. The supervising dentist need not be on
28 the premises.
