12 (3) (a) A licensed dental hygienist practicing under public health supervision may provide dental
13 hygiene preventative services that include removal of deposits and stains from the surfaces of teeth, the
14 application of topical fluoride, polishing restorations, root planing, placing of sealants, oral cancer screening,
15 exposing radiographs, charting of services provided, and prescriptive authority as allowed under 37-4-401(1)(c).
16 (b) A licensed dental hygienist practicing under public health supervision may not provide dental
17 hygiene preventative services that include local anesthesia, denture soft lines, temporary restorations, or any
18 other service prohibited under 37-4-401.
19 (c) A licensed dental hygienist practicing under public health supervision shall provide:
20 (i) for the referral to a licensed dentist of any patient needing treatment outside the scope of
21 practice authorized for a licensed dental hygienist under this subsection (4) (3); and
22 (ii) treatment based upon medical and dental health guidelines adopted by rule by the board.
23 (4) (a) A dental hygienist practicing under public health supervision shall obtain a limited access
24 permit from the board.
25 (b) The board shall adopt rules:
26 (i) defining the qualifications necessary to obtain a limited access permit; and
27 (ii) providing a process for obtaining a limited access permit.
28 (c) The provision of services under a limited access permit is limited to patients or residents of
